a Intelligence capability is the achievement of a framework for the success of data management projects by providing the routine and reusable architecture for measuring ROI and Risk, involving Data Ownership and Stewardship, developing data management processing, and delivering actionable Intelligence.</p>\r\n			\r\n			<ul class=\"sub-points\">\r\n				<li>Sustainable Data Intelligence perceives individual data management projects as integrated components of a successful, forward looking corporate framework that encompasses strategies and tools for:</li>\r\n					<ul>\r\n						<li>Data Governance</li>\r\n						<li>Data Quality Management</li>\r\n						<li>Master Data Management</li>\r\n						<li>Meta Data Management</li>\r\n						<li>Data Integration</li>\r\n						<li>Data Warehousing</li>\r\n						<li>Business Intelligence and Analytics</li>\r\n					</ul>\r\n			</ul>\r\n			\r\n			<p>BroadStreet Data understands the need to increase and justify the ROI on Sustainable Data Intelligence projects, especially in the current economic environment. Our approach is to study the existing SDI framework and propose a solution that maximizes return and identifies and isolates risk on return.  We provide technical solutions that are in tune with the targeted SDI capability, governance, ownership and support framework. BroadStreet Data proposes business solutions that target the gaps in the framework such as misalignment of business and IT goals, uncertain ownership, and management oversight. We are sensitive to customer culture and prefer to work directly in a team environment, which enhances communication, solution delivery, support and ultimately long term integration and acceptance.</p>','Our Methodology','','publish','open','open','','our-methodology','','','2010-03-14 06:33:04','2010-03-14 06:33:04','',6,'http://broadstreet.trusz.com/?page_id=13',1,'page','',0),(14,1,'2010-03-13 20:35:08','2010-03-13 20:35:08','','Our Methodology','','inherit','open','open','','13-revision','