r more complex DI Projects:</li>\r\n				<ul>\r\n					<li>Handling aggregation</li>\r\n					<li>Heterogeneous product and transaction types</li>\r\n					<li>Handling time and history, changing dimensions</li>\r\n					<li>Scheduling and error-handling</li>\r\n					<li>Late arriving data</li>\r\n					<li>Large scale database environments (MPP)</li>\r\n					<li>Integrating multiple complex data sources including XML and Web Services</li>\r\n					<li>Normalization and new modeling constructs</li>\r\n					<li>Identifying location and dimensional aspects of data</li>\r\n					<li>Extension and customization of commercial data models</li>\r\n					<li>Real-time and changed data capture Architectures</li>\r\n					<li>Operational BI real-time data consolidation and federation</li>\r\n					<li>Unstructured data connectivity (HL7, EDI, Excel, HTTP, etc.)</li>\r\n					<li>Legacy systems, conversion of manual code (COBOL, PL/SQL etc. to platform-based ETL solutions)</li>\r\n					<li>ETL developer, data architects, project managers, DQ specialists</li>\r\n				</ul>\r\n			</ul>','Data Integration & Quality','','publish','open','open','','data-integration-quality','','','2010-08-23 18:16:46','2010-08-23 18:16:46','',2,'http://broadstreet.trusz.com/?page_id=28',0,'page','',0),(29,1,'2010-03-13 20:39:37','2010-03-13 20:39:37','','Data Integration & Quality','','inherit','open','open','','28-revision','','','2010-03-13 20:39:37','2010-03-13 20:39:37','',28,'http://broadstreet.trusz.com/28-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(30,1,'2010-03-13 20:40:05','2010-03-13 20:40:05','<h2>Business Intelligence </h2>\r\n      <h3>Derive actionable information that empowers think tanks as well as stakeholders in daily operations with the necessary knowledge to make informed business decisions.</h3>\r\n      <p>A well-structured BI practice framework within an organization is often recognized across industries as the underlying enablement approach to align actionable, timely information with current and future corporate strategies, and equips decision makers with tactical knowledge to drive the overall success of their company. BroadStreet Data has the expertise of effective implementation methodologies and experience with industry leading tools to transform the &#8220;single source of truth&#8221; ideal into reality. Our customers benefit from an enhanced ability to analyze company health, measure quality, assess risk, reward employee accomplishment, capture and predict market behaviour, and posses a verifiable commercial perspective. We are positioned as the go-to solution services provider that fosters partnership with our customers and enriches their success.</p>\r\n      <ul class=\"sub-points\">\r\n        <li>Our consultants specialize in an array of BI tool sets including:</li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n<a href=ttp://www.sap.com/\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://wp.broadstreetdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/logo_SAP.gif\" alt=\"SAP\" title=\"SAP\" class=\"floatleft\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<a href=ttp://www.cognos.com/\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://wp.broadstreetdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/logo-cognos.gif\" alt=\"Cognos Software\" title=\"Cognos Software\"  class=\"floatleft\" /></a>	\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.microstrategy.com\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://wp.broadstreetdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/logo-microstrategy.gif\" alt=\"Microstrategy\" title=\"Microstrategy\"  class=\"floatleft\" /></a>	\r\n\r\n			<div class=\"clear\"></div>\r\n			\r\n      <ul class=\"sub-points\">\r\n        <li>Our BI related services include:</li>\r\n        <ul>\r\n          <li>Gap Analysis between ongoing business needs and current data availability</li>\r\n          <li>Application architecture design and implementation</li>\r\n          <li>BI Analytics &ndash; offering predictive analysis through historical trends, key performance indicators, relationships between drivers (revenue and cost modeling)</li>\r\n          <li>OLAP Design &ndash; enabling ad-hoc information access to answer real-time business questions</li>\r\n          <li>Development &ndash; pixel-perfect reports, strategic and operational dashboards, customized scorecards on overall health, flexible delivery channels (emails, alert trigger, bash distribution through platform)</li>\r\n          <li>Validation of measures against corporate and industry data governance policies</li>\r\n          <li>Metadata management</li>\r\n          <li>Scalable deployment (from globalized enterprises to SMBs)</li>\r\n          <li>Unified communication across departments and employee levels (eliminating proliferation of ambiguous and redundant business terms)</li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n      </ul>\r\n','Business Intelligence','','publish','open','open','','business-intelligence','','','2010-08-23 18:31:21','2010-08-23 18:31:21','',2,'http://broadstreet.trusz.com/?page_id=30',1,'page','',0),(31,1,'2010-03-13 20:40:03','2010-03-13 20:40:03','','Business Intelligence','','inherit','open','open','','30-revision','','','2010-03-13 20:40:03','2010-03-13 20:40:03','',30,'http://broadstreet.trusz.com/30-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(32,1,'2010-03-13 20:49:04','2010-03-13 20:49:04','<h2>Info Search & Access / Agile BI</h2><img src=\"http://wp.broadstreetdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/logo-endeca.jpg\" alt=\"\" title=\"logo-endeca\" width=\"115\" height=\"62\" class=\"floatright\" />\r\n			<h3>Combining the Ease-of-Search With The Analytic Power of BI to Deliver Game-Changing Results</h3>\r\n			<p>The demands on BI systems are changing significantly. Technology innovations, such as the Internet, email, video conferencing, and mobile technologies, have accelerated business communication across the enterprise and between the enterprise and their customers and partners. With business moving at a faster pace, the amount of business data generated, the number of data sources, and the variety of data types has also increased. To make informed decisions, people often must consider a broader set of data from a variety of systems. But because this data is so diverse, it defies conventional modeling. In addition, the new speed of business has caused consumers, partners, and employees alike to expect instant access to the information they need any time that they need it. </p>\r\n			\r\n	        <p>The charge for almost every IT and business intelligence (BI) organization today is to do more with less, and do it faster. Within BI organizations, the challenge is even greater - do all that, and also incorporate a myriad of new data sources, manage more complex data, and provide greater analytic capabilities to non-technical users.</p>\r\n	        <p>Endeca\'s solutions provide unparalleled discovery capabilities to business users and agility to IT organizations.</p>\r\n			<p>With discovery capabilities, users gain an intuitive and unconstrained approach to data analysis. This is essential for uncovering information hidden in data and driving game-changing business improvements. By combining ease-of-search with the analytic power of BI, Endeca\'s solutions bring discovery capabilities to all users.</p>','Info Search & Access/Agile BI','','publish','closed','closed','','agile-bi','','','2011-02-08 17:44:13','2011-02-08 17:44:13','',2,'http://broadstreet.trusz.com/?page_id=32',2,'page','',0),(33,1,'2010-03-13 20:49:01','2010-03-13 20:49:01','','Info Search Access','','inherit','open','open','','32-revision','','','2010-03-13 20:49:01','2010-03-13 20:49:01','',32,'http://broadstreet.trusz.com/32-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(34,1,'2010-03-13 20:49:41','2010-03-13 20:49:41','<h2>Master Data Management </h2>\r\n<h3>Rein in information distribution headaches, data quality nightmares, inconsistent classification and identification of data issues.</h3>\r\n<p>BroadStreet Data seeks to ensure that customers do not use multiple and potentially inconsistent versions of the same master data in different parts of their operations. This can occur naturally in large organizations. We partner with customers to develop the right data governance policies for their operations and design data architecture and build data integation tools which all combine to create a unified MDM platform. Our customers benefit from reduced effort, better productivity, shorter processing cycles, and consistent contacts and prospects.</p>\r\n<p>The successful implementation of an MDM solution involves a multi-disciplined approach. Data applications in complex environments are as diverse as the departments they serve and the technologies involved. An MDM solution must bring together the diverse systems and provide a uniform approach to consumption, processing, storage and distribution of master data.</p>\r\n			\r\n<ul class=\"sub-points\">\r\n<li>Our consultants are specialized in an array of MDM capabilities:</li>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Corporate Data Governance, Stewardship and Policy</li>\r\n	<li>Data Quality Management</li>\r\n	<li>Metadata Management</li>\r\n	<li>Data Integration Tools</li>\r\n	<li>Service Oriented Data Architecture</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n			\r\n			<ul class=\"sub-points\">\r\n				<li>Our MDM related services include:</li>\r\n					<ul>\r\n						<li>Data Asset and Business Process Analysis and Evaluation</li>\r\n						<li>Development of Data Governance policy and Stewardship</li>\r\n						<li>Master Data Identification, search and matching resolution</li>\r\n					    <li>Data Quality Assessment and process implementation</li>\r\n					    <li>Master Metadata integration</li>\r\n					    <li>MDM Data Modeling and Storage Design</li>\r\n					    <li>Data Integration ETL for Master Data migration and distribution</li>\r\n					    <li>Application Integration and Development for MDM processing, control and management</li>\r\n					</ul>\r\n			</ul>','Master Data Management','','publish','open','open','','master-data-management','','','2010-03-14 02:46:27','2010-03-14 02:46:27','',2,'http://broadstreet.trusz.com/?page_id=34',3,'page',''