this core asset.</strong>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Data Governance is the operational model for active management of the information asset.  It provides strategic direction to the business-driven policy making and oversight of corporate data.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">BDSI has a series of turnkey practical tools and methods that will allow your organization to actively manage its information and increase the value of this core asset. \r\nThis proven process results in:\r\n          •Improved data management  practices\r\n          •Business impact in the form of :\r\n                             •Accessibility, trust and realized value of data.\r\n                             •Maximized ROI for data assets\r\n                             •Reduced redundancy in data management services\r\n                             •Increased quality of data management services\r\n                             •Expanded adoption of common and shared data assets</p>\r\n\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align: justify;\">Governance Approaches</h4>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">•<strong>Passive Governance</strong> is a set of information standards and policies that an organization can use to manage specific points within its processes. </p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"> •<strong>Active Governance</strong> is the deliberate and structured method of managing information across its lifecycle through a coordinated set of organizational behaviours, standards and methods.<span id=\"_marker\"> </span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span><img class=\"size-full wp-image-916  aligncenter\" title=\"Data-Governance\" src=\"http://wp.broadstreetdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/09/Data-Governance.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"454\" height=\"545\" /></span></p>','Data Governance','','inherit','closed','closed','','910-revision-9','','','2010-09-09 18:39:17','2010-09-09 18:39:17','',910,'http://broadstreetdata.com/910-revision-9/',0,'revision','',0),(976,4,'2010-09-09 1